{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8b48ca7-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7362"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7362"},"text":"§ 7362.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Alcohol abuse and alcoholism","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b48ca8-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7362/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Office of Personnel Management shall be responsible for developing, in cooperation with the Secretary of Health and Human Services and with other agencies, and in accordance with applicable provisions of this subpart, appropriate prevention, treatment, and rehabilitation programs and services for alcohol abuse and alcoholism among employees. Such agencies are encouraged to extend, to the extent feasible, such programs and services to the families of alcoholic employees and to employees who have family members who are alcoholics. Such programs and services shall make optimal use of existing governmental facilities, services, and skills.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b48ca9-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7362/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Section 523 ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002137"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002137"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of the Public Health Service Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s290dd–3"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 290dd–3","children":[],"tail":"), relating to confidentiality of records, and any regulations prescribed thereunder, shall apply with respect to records maintained for the purpose of carrying out this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b48caa-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7362/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Each agency shall, with respect to any programs or services provided by such agency, submit such written reports as the Office may require in connection with any report required under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s7363"},"text":"section 7363 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8b48cab-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s7362/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" For the purpose of this section, the term “agency” means an Executive agency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8b48cac-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/570/tVI/s6002/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–570, title VI, § 6002(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3207-157"},"text":"100 Stat. 3207–157","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8b48cad-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8b48cae-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb8b48caf-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 523 of the Public Health Service Act, referred to in subsec. (b) and formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s290dd–3"},"text":"section 290dd–3 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, was renumbered section 544 of that Act by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/77/tVI/s611/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–77, title VI, § 611(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/516"},"text":"101 Stat. 516","children":[],"tail":" and then omitted in the general revision of Part D of Subchapter III–A of Chapter 6A of Title 42 by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/321/tI/s131"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–321, title I, § 131","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-07-10"},"text":"July 10, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/366"},"text":"106 Stat. 366","children":[],"tail":". Provisions relating to the confidentiality of patient records are now classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s290dd–2"},"text":"section 290dd–2 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
